org.obapanel.jedis.interruptinglocks

Class InterruptingJedisJedisLockExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.obapanel.jedis.interruptinglocks.AbstractInterruptingJedisLock
      • org.obapanel.jedis.interruptinglocks.InterruptingJedisJedisLockExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, IJedisLock

    public final class InterruptingJedisJedisLockExecutor
extends AbstractInterruptingJedisLock
    This class will use a executor to get a thread to wait for lease time to go zero CAUTION: the executor can prevent the interrupting operation to be launched, be aware not to use an exhausted pool For this reason, is recommended a cached thread pool, which will create bew threads on demand or will use old ones if avalible For example, with Executors.newCachedThreadPool()
